This folder is used for Splunk Universal Forwarder configuration in Docker Compose.

## Dynamic Templating (Recommended)

`outputs.conf.template` and `inputs.conf.template` are rendered at container startup using environment variables (via `envsubst`).

- Place variables in your `secrets.env` or Docker Compose `environment` block.
- Use `${VARNAME}` syntax in the `.template` files.
- The rendered files are written to `/opt/splunkforwarder/etc/system/local/outputs.conf` and `inputs.conf` inside the container.

**Do not mount static `outputs.conf` or `inputs.conf` directly.**

### Example `outputs.conf.template`

```
[tcpout]
defaultGroup=default-autolb-group

[tcpout:default-autolb-group]
server=${SPLUNK_INDEXER}:${SPLUNK_PORT}

[tcpout-server://${SPLUNK_INDEXER}:${SPLUNK_PORT}]
[indexAndForward]
index = false
```

### Example `inputs.conf.template`

```
[monitor:///app/logs/spring.log]
sourcetype=${SPLUNK_SOURCETYPE}
index=${SPLUNK_INDEX}
disabled = false
```

## Legacy/Static Config (Not Recommended)

If you want to use static config, mount `outputs.conf` or `inputs.conf` directly, but this disables dynamic templating.

## Files

- `outputs.conf.template` — Template for outputs config (use env vars)
- `inputs.conf.template` — Template for inputs config (use env vars)
- `outputs.conf` — (Optional) Static config, not used with templating
- `inputs.conf` — (Optional) Static config, not used with templating
- `server.conf`, `web.conf` — Optional Splunk config files
- `entrypoint.sh` — No longer needed (remove)

